## M2 — Pattern from #229 confirmed + applied to all 5 sites

Diff shape (per site, mirrors v1.80.10 inline pattern):

```ts
// BEFORE
const userId = (session as { userId?: string | null }).userId ?? null
if (!userId) throw new Error('Admin sessions cannot ...')

// AFTER
const sessionUserId = (session as { userId?: string | null }).userId ?? null
const sessionLineId = session.lineId || null
if (!sessionUserId && !sessionLineId) {
  throw new Error('Sign in with a player account to ...')
}
let user: { id: ... } | null = null
if (sessionUserId) user = await prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id: sessionUserId }, ... })
if (!user && sessionLineId) user = await prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { lineId: sessionLineId }, ... })
if (!user) throw new Error('User not found')
const userId = user.id
```

`completeOnboardingWithId` additionally folds the v1.78.0 `userRow`
email lookup into the resolved `user` row's select clause, eliminating
one redundant DB round-trip.

`redeemInvite` additionally resolves `lineId` from `user.lineId`
(canonical, User.lineId @unique) rather than the session, so
`linkUserToPlayer` writes the right value when the LINE-auth admin path
is taken.

All five sites preserve the downstream `userId` variable name (just
sourced from `user.id` post-resolution), so no other call sites needed
changing.

